single parents did you support yourself and go go college my kids are and we are so broke its deprressing i get very little support from my ex and i need a way to make ends meet everyone says college is the answer i can see that after you finish how nice it would be but when you're going if i cant even support us now how can i support us and pay for whatever expenses college costs that financial aid doesn't cover i guess my question is single moms how did you do it on your own because i dont see a way i took out loans and lived very frugally it was tough but it's one of the things i'm most proud of i worked hard got my accounting degree and went to work it was worth it and those times are some i remember with great fondness it was just us three and we were broke but we were happy don't be embarassed to look into wic or some kind of aid that's what it's there for to help until you get your feet on the ground Student loan Humphrey Bogart Rent (musical) Little Britain Theory of conduct Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME Rich Mullins Microeconomics Life insurance The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Insurance Gross domestic product Small business Education in the People's Republic of China Nine Inch Nails You Don't Know Jack Kyle Broflovski Pitaten Sampling (music) Philosophical skepticism Extreme Programming Hyperinflation Password CPU cache Divorce Shaggy dog story Personal finance Goodness and value theory Evan Mecham Capital accumulation Kurt Cobain The Ashlee Simpson Show EastEnders Cindy Sheehan Teresa Heinz Kerry The Fairly OddParents Calvin and Hobbes Avenue Q 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Shit Education in the United States Samuel Goldwyn Credit card Poker jargon Drill bit GED Lance Armstrong Piccolo Junior Saga Aerial (dance move) Adoption The nature of God in Western theology Welfare Wheel of Fortune Deflation (economics) Michael Jackson 401(k) The writing of Principia Mathematica The Isley Brothers Graduate school Quizbowl Lorelai Gilmore Atomic Kitten Tuition